						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1443, Vṛisha, Chaitra, śu. 1,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1521 March 9, Saturday</hi> (not verifiable), in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Kṛishṇadēva-Mahārāya.</hi> It records that while <hi rend="bold">Kaṭṭige Kāmaṇa-Nāyaka</hi> was in charge of the fortress of <hi rend="bold">Ādavāni,</hi> his <hi rend="italic">Maṇehagāra,</hi> <hi rend="bold">Chiṅkala Tirumalabōva,</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Sēnabōva</hi> <hi rend="bold">Timmarasa</hi> issued certain orders regarding the manufacture of salt in some villages (named), belonging to <hi rend="bold">Aḍapada Mācha</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Mīnagondi</hi> in Ādavāni (division).</p>						

						<p>First Face.</p>						

						</summary>
